Bemar Plast specializes in the subcontracting of thermoplastic components through:

• Injection molding (13 presses from 10 to 480 tons);
• 3D printing (FDM and MJF);
• Design and construction of molds.

 Bemar Plast works based on six cornerstones:

• consolidated experience in the sector;
• high quality of both processes and products;
• flexibility of the services offered;
• punctuality of deliveries;
• attention to the eco-sustainability of materials and processes;
• the competence and availability of the staff.

 Bemar Plast is ISO 9001:2015 certified

ITIB was founded in 1946 to produce impregnated cardboard pipes. In more than 70 years’ activity, ITIB, through a continuous technological upgrade, has reached levels of experience that allow to operate as partner with many European industrial groups.

Since the 60s ITIB has experienced and developed a deep knowledge in extrusion machines to produce  corrugated flexible pipes in thermoplastic material and in the production of plastic technical items obtained from blow-moulding technology.

ITIB is able to satisfy all the specific customers’ requests, from design to execution. In order to complete the products’ range, the extrusion technology of smooth pipes in thermoplastic material has been added.

Thanks to the collaboration with first level industrial partners, ITIB can offer complementary technologies to the transformation of the polymer as:

• thermo-forming of smooth or corrugated pipes;

• machining of blow-moulding ducts;

• vibration or hot-blade welding of injection and/or blow molded components;

• components’ automatic assembling;

• 100% air leakage test;

• 100% automatic visual control;

By the historical headquarter in Paderno Franciacorta near Brescia, from 2001 stands the productive site of Międzyrzecze Górne in the neighbourhoods of Bielsko Biala in Poland.

Placed in the higher industrial density area in Poland, ITIB offers a strategic local service able to supply quality products at competitive costs.

Today ITIB works with acknowledged competences and reliability in automotive field, household appliances and construction area. The demands coming from these primary markets allow ITIB to reply successfully to specific requests of any sectors in which experience and “at the state of art” technology represent keynotes.

